        Check if there is another row available.

      • hasNextSheet

        boolean hasNextSheet()
        Determines whether or not the underlying excel workbook has another worksheet after this one. If the underlying data source is not an excel workbook, this will always return false.
        Returns:

      • getSheetName

        java.lang.String getSheetName()
        Returns the name of the current sheet over which this DataDriver is iterating. If the underlying data source is not an excel workbook, this will always return null.
        Returns:

        java.lang.String[] next()
        Gets the next row. Behavior is undefined if hasNext would return false.

      • nextRow

        DataRow nextRow()
        Gets the next row. Behavior is undefined if hasNext would return false.
        Returns:
        The row as a DataRow object.

      • nextSheet

        boolean nextSheet()
        Advances the underlying excel workbook to the next sheet. If the underlying data source is not an excel workbook, this does nothing
